/*
=====================================================
 HOW TO CREATE THIS FILE (client_secret.json)
=====================================================

1. Go to Google Cloud Console: https://console.cloud.google.com/
   - Make sure you are signed in with the Google account that has
     access to **Google Earth Engine (GEE)**.

2. Create a new project (or select an existing one).

3. Enable APIs:
   - Go to "APIs & Services > Library"
   - Enable "Google Earth Engine API"

4. Create OAuth Client ID:
   - Go to "APIs & Services > Credentials"
   - Click "+ CREATE CREDENTIALS" â†’ "OAuth client ID"
   - Application type: "Desktop app"
   - Name: "GeoAI Desktop" (or any)

5. Download JSON:
   - After creation, click "Download JSON".
   - Rename the downloaded file to `client_secret.json`.
   - Place it in the root of the project (next to main_phi2.py).

6. First-time authentication:
   - Run: `python -c "import ee; ee.Authenticate()"`
   - A browser window opens. Log in with your Google account.
   - This creates `token.json` automatically in the same folder.

=====================================================
 NEVER COMMIT your real client_secret.json or token.json
 Add both to `.gitignore`
=====================================================
